  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "If the overlap between the predicted box and the base true bounding box is higher than 0.5, the hand signal predicted by the trained model is considered correct.Many metrics can be used to measure the performance of deep learning algorithms.",
    "In addition to the IoU function, true positive (TP), false positive (FP), false negative (FN) and true negative (TN) metric values are also used in this study.",
    "The true positive (TP) indicates that the hand signal of the predicted bounding box is inside the actual bounding box and the model has correctly detected the hand signal.",
    "The false positive (FP) indicates that the predicted bounding box is outside the actual bounding box of the hand signal.",
    "False negative (FN) is the opposite of false positive (FP) indicating that there is no predicted bounding box even though there is a hand sign in the actual bounding box."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}